    "content" : "你是一个专业的网络资源整理师，负责根据用户的网站建设需求，**主动积极地使用工具**搜集和整理可直接用于网站内容的文本素材。\n\n## 可调用工具\n\n1. **AiWebSearchTool**：搜索与用户需求相关的网络资源（文章、数据、信息等）\n2. **AiWebScrapingTool**：抓取并解析指定网页的内容\n\n## 核心任务\n\n**必须主动调用工具**搜集与用户需求相关的网络资源，整理出可直接用于网站内容展示的素材文档（文字、数据、链接等）。\n\n**重要原则：**\n- 只要用户需求涉及网站建设（而非代码修改），就应该**积极尝试调用工具**搜集素材\n- 即使需求看似简单，也要尝试搜索相关行业资料、案例、数据等，为网站内容提供丰富素材\n- 优先使用 **AiWebSearchTool** 进行广泛搜索，再根据需要使用 **AiWebScrapingTool** 深入抓取\n\n**工具调用次数限制（重要）：**\n- **最多调用 1-2 次工具**，避免过度搜索导致生成时间过长\n- 每次搜索使用**精准、高质量的关键词**，一次性获取足够信息\n- 优先选择 1-2 个最核心的搜索关键词，而非多次尝试不同关键词\n- 如果前 2 次搜索已获得足够素材，**立即停止**，不要继续搜索\n- 控制原则：**质量优先于数量**，精准搜索优于广泛搜索\n\n## 整理规范\n\n### 1. 素材分类与结构\n- 按主题或网站模块分组（如\"关于我们\"、\"产品介绍\"、\"新闻动态\"等）\n- 每组素材包含：标题、正文要点、关键数据、引用语等\n\n### 2. 文本素材\n- 提取关键内容，去除冗余，确保文本简洁清晰\n- 较长文本提供摘要或要点列表\n- 注明来源以保持准确性\n\n### 3. URL 素材\n- 提供完整可访问的链接，附带简要描述\n- 优先选择权威来源（官方网站、知名媒体）\n\n### 4. 输出格式\n- 使用 Markdown 格式整理素材，便于后续直接拼接到代码生成提示词中\n- 使用列表或表格形式组织，增强可读性\n- 按主题分节，结构清晰\n- 素材应全面但精简，只包括与用户需求高度相关的内容\n\n### 5. 质量控制\n- 优先选择权威、最新的来源\n- 交叉验证信息以确保准确性\n- 保持中立客观，避免偏见或促销性内容\n\n## 特殊情况\n\n如果用户需求是网站/代码的修改需求，或与网站建设无关，或确实无法找到合适的网络资源，直接输出\"无\"，不要有任何额外输出。"
  }, {
    "role" : "user",
    "content" : "创建一个网页，用于我给我的老板总结本周工作成果。\n成果包含：\n本周我完成了以下内容——\n主导了618大促预售活动策划，完成目标销售额1200万，超预期15%。\n\n优化了广告投放策略，ROI提升至3.2，点击率提升20%。\n\n上线了“会员日”新玩法，会员复购率环比提升8%。\n\n推动与3家头部KOL达成合作，带来新增用户5万人。\n\n完成了首页改版，重点品类曝光提升25%。\n\n团队培训两场，提升客服转化率10%等。\n\n完成了竞争对手分析报告，制定了下阶段的定价策略。\n\n协调供应链，确保爆款库存充足，售罄率控制在90%。"
  }, {
    "role" : "assistant",
    "content" : "我将为您创建一个专业、简洁的本周工作成果总结网页。首先，我需要搜索一些关于职场汇报网页设计的最佳实践和模板，以便为您提供更专业的设计方案。\n\n",
    "tool_calls" : [ {
      "id" : "call_500e12582916402a916436",
      "type" : "function",
      "function" : {
        "name" : "searchWeb",
        "arguments" : "{\"query\": \"professional weekly work report webpage design best practices html css\"}"
      }
    } ]
  }, {
    "role" : "tool",
    "tool_call_id" : "call_500e12582916402a916436",
    "content" : "[{\"id\":1,\"title\":\"Web Design Best Practices For Your Next Website Project in 2026\",\"link\":\"https://elementor.com/blog/web-design-best-practices/\",\"snippet\":\" Clarity and Simplicity:The website’s purpose and navigation should be immediately obvious. A cluttered or confusing layout leads to frustration and high bounce rates. Mobile Compatibility:With over 60% of website traffic coming from mobile devices, a seamless experience on smartphones and tablets is essential. Security:Users need to feel that their data is safe, especially onecommerceor lead generation sites. A visible SSL certificate (HTTPS) is a basic requirement. Personalization:While not always possible for every site, users appreciate content and offers that are relevant to their interests and past behavior. The Role of User Intent in Web Design Understandingwhya user is visiting your site is as important as knowingwhothey are. User intent can generally be broken down into four categories:\",\"date\":\"2025-11-11 16:21:46\"},{\"id\":2,\"title\":\"Design Trends\",\"link\":\"https://elementor.com/blog/tendances-et-meilleures-pratiques-en-matiere-de-conception-web-pour-2025/\",\"snippet\":\" The complete website building experience. Create, optimize, and manage in one subscription. A single, unified experience Bank of shared credits across capabilities\",\"date\":\"2025-07-22 14:28:25\"},{\"id\":3,\"title\":\"Build a Webpage with HTML and CSS | Coursera\",\"link\":\"https://www.coursera.org/programs/coursera-for-university-of-rochester-mdtfv/learn/build-a-webpage-with-html-and-css?authMode=login\",\"snippet\":\"build website with html, javascript, angularjs, and react专项课程 单元 评价 审阅 您将学到什么 build website with html, javascript, angularjs, and react专项课程 该课程共有3个模块 thebuild a webpage with html and csscourse is designed for complete beginners who want to learn how to create a web page, even with no prior coding experience. you'll discover how to structure content using html, style your site with css, and apply responsive design principles with bootstrap—all while building a real, shareable web page from scratch. in the first module, you'll explore the fundamentals of html, including document structure, essential tags, and how to organize content for clarity and accessibility. you'll learn how to use html to create headings, lists, images, links, tables, and forms, and understand the importance of clean, well-nested code.the second module focuses on css, teaching you how to style and format your web page using selectors, properties, and advanced features like flexbox and grid. you'll master how to control layout, typography, and color, and see how css can transform a basic html page into a visually engaging website.the final module introduces bootstrap, a powerful \",\"date\":\"2026-02-20 17:20:20\"},{\"id\":4,\"title\":\"Best Web Design Practices: UI/UX, Hierarchy, and More (2026)\",\"link\":\"https://www.hostinger.com/tutorials/web-design-best-practices\",\"snippet\":\" Audience analysis. Research your audience’s demographics and psychographics. This includes information like your audience’s age range, gender, location, socioeconomic status, interests, and lifestyle choices. Client interview. Invite people who have already bought your product or service to an interview. In addition to providing insights about the kind of person they are and why they chose your product, it also helps to strengthen connections with your audience.\",\"date\":\"2026-02-16 12:36:20\"},{\"id\":5,\"title\":\"html网页设计 静态网页制作 web毕设 大作业设计\",\"link\":\"https://zhuanlan.zhihu.com/p/589373565\",\"snippet\":\" ( 1)html文件:其中index.html是首页、其他html为二级页面; ( 2)css文件:css全部页面样式,文字滚动, 图片放大等; ( 3)js文件:js实现动态轮播特效, 表单提交, 点击事件等等(网页中运用到js代码)\",\"date\":\"2022-12-17 20:47:00\"},{\"id\":6,\"title\":\"Best Practices for Working with HTML Code in Microsoft FrontPage version 2002\",\"link\":\"https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/previous-versions/office/developer/office-xp/aa140086(v%3doffice.10)\",\"snippet\":\" Experience with authoring Web pages,\",\"date\":\"2002-03-18 19:04:44\"},{\"id\":7,\"title\":\"Learner Reviews & Feedback for Build a Webpage with HTML and CSS Course | Coursera\",\"link\":\"https://www.coursera.org/programs/dc-4-learning-program-zbgra/learn/build-a-webpage-with-html-and-css/reviews\",\"snippet\":\"thebuild a webpage with html and csscourse is designed for complete beginners who want to learn how to create a web page, even with no prior coding experience. you'll discover how to structure content using html, style your site with css, and apply responsive design principles with bootstrap—all while building a real, shareable web page from scratch.in the first module, you'll explore the fundamentals of html, including document structure, essential tags, and how to organize content for clarity and accessibility. you'll learn how to use html to create headings, lists, images, links, tables, and forms, and understand the importance of clean, well-nested code.the second module focuses on css, teaching you how to style and format your web page using selectors, properties, and advanced features like flexbox and grid. you'll master how to control layout, typography, and color, and see how css can transform a basic html page into a visually engaging website.the final module introduces bootstrap, a powerful framework for building responsive, mobile-friendly websites. you'll work with bootstrap's pre-built components, grid system, and utilities to create professional-looking layouts that adapt to any device. by the end, you'll have a fully functional, modern web page and the foundational skills to start a website or pursue further web development.by the end of this course, you will confidently:1. build and structure web pages using html tags, elements, and attributes2. style and format your web page with css for layout, colors, and typography3. create responsive, professional websites using bootstrap's components and grid system4. apply web design best practices to ensure your site is visually appealing and accessible5. share a real, working web page as part of your portfolio or online presencethis course is ideal for those who:- \",\"date\":\"2024-02-21 00:00:00\"},{\"id\":8,\"title\":\"Build a Webpage with HTML and CSS | Coursera\",\"link\":\"https://www.coursera.org/programs/dc-2-learning-program-dljqh/learn/build-a-webpage-with-html-and-css\",\"snippet\":\" 探索 登录 Build a Webpage with HTML and CSS 注册 于2月16日 开始 关于 结果 单元 评价 审阅 从Computer Science 浏览更多内容 Board Infinity JavaScript for Web Development\",\"date\":\"2026-02-16 01:57:06\"},{\"id\":9,\"title\":\"What Is CSS? How to Use it in Web Design (2026)\",\"link\":\"https://elementor.com/blog/what-is-css/\",\"snippet\":\" Selectors:Selectors are like special instructions for your browser, telling it which specific HTML elements you want to style. Common types of selectors includeElement selectors, Class selectors,andID selectors.\",\"date\":\"2025-11-03 17:53:21\"},{\"id\":10,\"title\":\"HTML Font Styles – How to Style Text in HTML\",\"link\":\"https://www.bluehost.com/blog/html-font-styles/\",\"snippet\":\"HTML Font Styles – How to Style Text in HTML Key highlights Discover how HTML font style choices impact readability, user experience and the overall professional feel of your website. Learn the main categories of fonts in HTML, including serif, sans-serif, monospace, cursive and fantasy, with clear use cases. Explore the most reliable web-safe fonts for HTML and see how to build font stacks that work across browsers and devices. Implement custom fonts in HTML using CSS font-family, Google Fonts and @font-face while keeping performance and loading speed in check. Apply best practices for HTML font style and choose fonts for HTML that balance aesthetics, accessibility and consistent branding. Fonts are like the outfits of your web page—dress it well and visitors stay; dress it poorly and they leave faster than a slow-loading page. A well-chosen HTML font style plays an important role in enhancing readability, improving user experience and adding a professional touch to your site. The right typography can make or break a website’s visual appeal, influencing how users engage with your content. Think about the last time you visited a website with difficult-to-read fonts—did you stay or click away? Choosing the right HTML text formatting ensures clarity, making the content accessible and aesthetically pleasing. Whether you’re designing a blog, an eCommerce store or a portfolio, understanding how to style fonts effectively is crucial. In this guide, we’ll explore different HTML font families, how to apply them using CSS and best practices to make your content shine. By the end, you’ll have a solid grasp of how to use them effectively to enhance your website’s design and functionality. Understanding HTML font style categories Fonts are generally categorized into five major typefaces, each serving different design needs for both print content and digital use: Serif\",\"date\":\"2025-11-18 19:30:48\"}]"
  } ],
